{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17607834","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17607834"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:26:53+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:26:53+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15969"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15969","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15969"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.57,0.36,0,0,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8660"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71162"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8660","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8660"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15969"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56633"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"23"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"11061"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20736"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20740"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71162","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/71162"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EPre-eclampsia is a pregnancy-specific disorder characterised by new-onset hypertension and end-organ dysfunction after 20 weeks gestation. The condition begins with abnormal placental development in early pregnancy.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the key placental abnormality in pre-eclampsia?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Insufficient spiral artery remodelling","Excessive spiral artery remodelling","Complete absence of spiral arteries","Normal spiral arteries with increased placental mass","Reversed flow in spiral arteries"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn normal pregnancy, maternal spiral arteries undergo extensive remodelling to become wide, low-resistance vessels that can adequately perfuse the developing placenta. In pre-eclampsia, \u003Cstrong\u003Einsufficient spiral artery remodelling\u003C/strong\u003E occurs, leading to reduced placental perfusion and subsequent maternal endothelial dysfunction.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExcessive spiral artery remodelling\u003C/strong\u003E would actually improve placental perfusion and is not seen in pre-eclampsia\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EComplete absence of spiral arteries\u003C/strong\u003E is not compatible with pregnancy\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENormal spiral arteries with increased placental mass\u003C/strong\u003E does not explain the pathophysiology of pre-eclampsia\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReversed flow in spiral arteries\u003C/strong\u003E is not a feature of pre-eclampsia\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe inadequate remodelling of spiral arteries results in placental hypoperfusion, oxidative stress, and release of inflammatory factors that cause widespread maternal endothelial dysfunction.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Pre-eclampsia involves inadequate remodelling of maternal spiral arteries during early pregnancy.","Normal placentation requires transformation of spiral arteries into wide, low-resistance vessels.","Insufficient spiral artery remodelling leads to placental hypoperfusion and maternal endothelial dysfunction."],"references":["Fox R, Kitt J, Leeson P, Aye CYL, Lewandowski AJ. Preeclampsia: Risk Factors, Diagnosis, Management, and the Cardiovascular Impact on the Offspring. J Clin Med. 2019 Oct 4;8(10):1625. doi: 10.3390/jcm8101625. PMID: 31590294; PMCID: PMC6832549","Uzan J, Carbonnel M, Piconne O, Asmar R, Ayoubi JM. Pre-eclampsia: pathophysiology, diagnosis, and management. Vasc Health Risk Manag. 2011;7:467-74. doi: 10.2147/VHRM.S20181. Epub 2011 Jul 19. PMID: 21822394; PMCID: PMC3148420","Arulkumaran, S., Ledger, W., Denny, L., \u0026 Doumouchtsis, S. (Eds.). (2019). Oxford Textbook of Obstetrics and Gynaecology. Oxford University Press","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56633"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15969"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56633","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56633"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-17T15:43:37+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-02T08:23:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8660"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"71162"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"23","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/23"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd30","name":"Obstetrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"typ